00:09:18.630 --> 00:09:20.760
So the low energy limit,
as we said before,

00:09:20.760 --> 00:09:23.420
just has to be super gravity.

00:09:23.420 --> 00:09:26.210
So it has to be super gravity.

00:09:26.210 --> 00:09:29.990
Then you find you actually
have exactly the same amount

00:09:29.990 --> 00:09:32.480
of supersymmetry
in this geometry.

00:09:36.940 --> 00:09:42.170
But the interesting thing
is that by definition,

00:09:42.170 --> 00:09:45.700
the supersymmetry on the
gravity side is actually local.

00:09:45.700 --> 00:09:47.200
So you actually
have the same amount

00:09:47.200 --> 00:09:48.490
of local supersymmetries.

00:10:07.450 --> 00:10:09.650
So if you look at
this correspondence

00:10:09.650 --> 00:10:19.052
between each other, then
you actually see a pattern.

00:10:19.052 --> 00:10:20.385
So now let me make some remarks.

00:10:26.170 --> 00:10:29.570
So if you look at the
structure, this math in here,

00:10:29.570 --> 00:10:30.387
you see a pattern.

00:10:34.050 --> 00:10:35.940
On this side, all
these symmetries

00:10:35.940 --> 00:10:37.101
are global symmetries.

00:10:39.870 --> 00:10:41.510
But on this side,
all these symmetries

00:10:41.510 --> 00:10:44.880
are local symmetries.

00:10:44.880 --> 00:10:47.440
So this, I just said
that in super gravity,

00:10:47.440 --> 00:10:50.540
the supersymmetry is local.

00:10:50.540 --> 00:10:59.080
And the space time isometry
is just subset of a space time

00:10:59.080 --> 00:11:01.110
coordinate transformation.

00:11:01.110 --> 00:11:05.760
And space time
coordinate transformation

00:11:05.760 --> 00:11:08.810
are local symmetries.

00:11:08.810 --> 00:11:19.440
So the isometry is a
subgroup of diffeomorphism.

00:11:24.340 --> 00:11:27.410
So diffeomorphism just means
the coordinate transformations.

00:11:30.194 --> 00:11:31.485
And these are local symmetries.

00:11:48.580 --> 00:11:52.580
Now we find the mapping is
on the field theory side,

00:11:52.580 --> 00:12:00.820
the global symmetries is
mapped on the gravity side

00:12:00.820 --> 00:12:02.065
into the local symmetries.

00:12:09.810 --> 00:12:12.040
So for each global symmetry
in the field theory side,

00:12:12.040 --> 00:12:14.498
there's a corresponding local
symmetry on the gravity side.

00:12:21.200 --> 00:12:25.500
But you may immediately ask the
question, on the gravity side,

00:12:25.500 --> 00:12:26.940
if you talk about
diffeomorphism,

00:12:26.940 --> 00:12:30.050
then this is a huge
group-- certainly much,

00:12:30.050 --> 00:12:33.330
much larger than what we are
talking about the isometry

00:12:33.330 --> 00:12:34.160
here.

00:12:34.160 --> 00:12:35.910
So why we are only
talking about isometry?

00:12:41.334 --> 00:12:43.750
Why we don't talk about other
parts of the diffeomorphism,

00:12:43.750 --> 00:12:44.791
only talk about isometry?

00:12:47.579 --> 00:12:49.120
So what's special
about the isometry?

00:12:52.910 --> 00:12:56.480
So the second
remark, why isometry?

00:13:02.430 --> 00:13:03.180
Why only isometry?

00:13:05.930 --> 00:13:07.230
Why only look at the isometry?

00:13:07.230 --> 00:13:09.250
But let me just save time.

00:13:14.430 --> 00:13:23.970
So the isometry is important
for the following reason.

00:13:23.970 --> 00:13:29.180
Because even though this
is a subgroup-- so as

00:13:29.180 --> 00:13:32.480
I mentioned last time, when
we talk about quantum gravity,

00:13:32.480 --> 00:13:36.240
when we talk about string theory
and Anti-de Sitter times S5

00:13:36.240 --> 00:13:41.140
in terms of AdS5 times S5,
you should keep in mind

00:13:41.140 --> 00:13:46.091
that this AdS5 times S5 refers
to the asymptotic geometry.

00:13:46.091 --> 00:13:47.715
Because as a quantum
theory, the theory

00:13:47.715 --> 00:13:49.020
can fluctuate in the middle.

00:13:52.040 --> 00:13:54.540
And the isometry can be
considered as a subgroup.

00:13:59.300 --> 00:14:03.990
But the level is even though
the space time fluctuates,

00:14:03.990 --> 00:14:07.940
but the AdS5 times S5 specifies
the asymptotic geometry

00:14:07.940 --> 00:14:09.080
of the space time.

00:14:13.820 --> 00:14:19.180
And the isometry is
precisely the subgroup

00:14:19.180 --> 00:14:34.290
which leaves the asymptotic
form of the metric invariant.

00:14:46.260 --> 00:14:50.670
So these are not
ordinary diffeomorphisms.

00:14:50.670 --> 00:14:53.630
So the ordinary
diffeomorphisms--

00:14:53.630 --> 00:14:55.260
so ordinary gauge
transformations,

00:14:55.260 --> 00:14:57.520
let me just say more generally.

00:14:57.520 --> 00:15:02.080
By gauge transformations,
also means the diffeomorphism

00:15:02.080 --> 00:15:05.480
or just general gauge
transformations.

00:15:05.480 --> 00:15:09.450
So when we talk about
gauge transformations, say

00:15:09.450 --> 00:15:12.630
for example, in QED
or in QCD, et cetera,

00:15:12.630 --> 00:15:20.430
we always assume-- so the
classical gauge transformation,

00:15:20.430 --> 00:15:23.920
we can see that we always
take them to be fall off

00:15:23.920 --> 00:15:25.310
sufficiently fast at infinity.

00:15:44.420 --> 00:15:46.520
When we talk about
gauge transformations,

00:15:46.520 --> 00:15:51.090
when we talk about the
typical diffeomorphisms,

00:15:51.090 --> 00:15:53.800
these are the kind of
transformations we assume

00:15:53.800 --> 00:15:56.110
goes to 1, say, at infinity.

00:15:59.850 --> 00:16:03.370
And this isometry, which
leaves the asymptotic

00:16:03.370 --> 00:16:07.147
over the metric invariant,
so these are essentially

00:16:07.147 --> 00:16:08.480
the large gauge transformations.

00:16:20.760 --> 00:16:22.430
So-called large
transformations is

00:16:22.430 --> 00:16:26.880
that they don't go to
the Identity at infinity.

00:16:26.880 --> 00:16:31.770
And of course, this is precisely
the large gauge transformations

00:16:31.770 --> 00:16:34.580
which leaves the
asymptotic invariant.

00:16:37.420 --> 00:16:42.310
So in a sense, these large
gauge transformations

00:16:42.310 --> 00:16:55.800
can be considered as the global
part of the diffeomorphism.

