00:17:57.440 --> 00:17:59.440
AUDIENCE: What happens
to gauge transformations

00:17:59.440 --> 00:18:01.789
in the Yang-Mills part?

00:18:01.789 --> 00:18:02.330
HONG LIU: No.

00:18:02.330 --> 00:18:04.330
The gauge transformation
in the Yang-Mills part,

00:18:04.330 --> 00:18:06.690
you don't see it.

00:18:06.690 --> 00:18:08.400
Gauge freedom is just
redundant freedom.

00:18:08.400 --> 00:18:11.870
You never see it
on the other side.

00:18:11.870 --> 00:18:16.295
AUDIENCE: Does this list
exhaust all symmetries

00:18:16.295 --> 00:18:17.570
of the Yang-Mills particle?

00:18:17.570 --> 00:18:19.984
HONG LIU: Yeah.

00:18:19.984 --> 00:18:23.584
Exhausts all global symmetries
in the Yang-Mills theory part.

00:18:23.584 --> 00:18:25.876
AUDIENCE: Not local?

00:18:25.876 --> 00:18:27.250
HONG LIU: All the
global theories

00:18:27.250 --> 00:18:30.345
on the Yang-Mills side,
and not local symmetries.

00:18:30.345 --> 00:18:33.990
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]
discuss them, [INAUDIBLE].

00:18:33.990 --> 00:18:36.670
HONG LIU: There's a
u(n) gauge group there,

00:18:36.670 --> 00:18:38.890
but they don't have
correspondence in the gravity

00:18:38.890 --> 00:18:41.080
side.

00:18:41.080 --> 00:18:43.840
The reason we don't consider
the gauge symmetry, because they

00:18:43.840 --> 00:18:46.060
correspond to
redundancies and they

00:18:46.060 --> 00:18:48.869
don't have to be present
on the other side.

00:18:48.869 --> 00:18:51.410
You only need to do the physical
[INAUDIBLE] to be identical.

00:18:51.410 --> 00:18:56.960
And this also is the reason
I make this remark here.

00:18:56.960 --> 00:18:59.860
Even though all these
global symmetries,

00:18:59.860 --> 00:19:01.710
they find the corresponding
local symmetries

00:19:01.710 --> 00:19:04.210
on the gravity side.

00:19:04.210 --> 00:19:10.160
But precisely due
to this remark,

00:19:10.160 --> 00:19:14.160
those things which really
map to the global symmetries

00:19:14.160 --> 00:19:15.850
in the field theory
can be considered

00:19:15.850 --> 00:19:20.759
as a global part of the local
symmetries on the gravity side.

00:19:20.759 --> 00:19:22.550
So even on the gravity
side, in some sense,

00:19:22.550 --> 00:19:24.750
you should think of them
as global symmetries.

00:19:24.750 --> 00:19:30.622
And they are large
gauge transformations.

00:19:30.622 --> 00:19:32.330
Because the ordinary
gauge transformation

00:19:32.330 --> 00:19:36.290
is just corresponding
to redundancy

00:19:36.290 --> 00:19:37.490
of degrees of freedom.

00:19:37.490 --> 00:19:40.265
And that should not be
reflected on the other side.

00:19:40.265 --> 00:19:42.640
