00:19:49.980 --> 00:19:55.400
just like in QED, in quantum
electrodynamics, when we talk

00:19:55.400 --> 00:19:57.600
about gauge transformation.

00:19:57.600 --> 00:20:00.490
The gauge transformations
we consider all the gauge

00:20:00.490 --> 00:20:02.842
transformations which
go to zero at infinity.

00:20:02.842 --> 00:20:04.800
And if you consider those
gauge transformations

00:20:04.800 --> 00:20:06.860
which don't go to
zero at infinity,

00:20:06.860 --> 00:20:09.210
and that's what we call
large gauge transformations.

00:20:09.210 --> 00:20:11.460
And those large gauge
transformations essentially

00:20:11.460 --> 00:20:16.510
is like the global part of
the u(1) gauge symmetry,

00:20:16.510 --> 00:20:18.190
in some sense can
be considered as.

00:20:21.130 --> 00:20:25.980
AUDIENCE: But that is the gauge
symmetry being gravity side.

00:20:25.980 --> 00:20:27.010
HONG LIU: That's right.

00:20:27.010 --> 00:20:33.380
So this is the part of the gauge
symmetry on the gravity side.

00:20:33.380 --> 00:20:36.510
But the part corresponding
to the boundary

00:20:36.510 --> 00:20:38.245
is the part associated
with the infinity.

00:20:44.190 --> 00:20:47.270
AUDIENCE: Here in
isometry of AdS5,

00:20:47.270 --> 00:20:49.580
we were showing,
like in p-set, it's

00:20:49.580 --> 00:20:51.980
point to point local symmetry.

00:20:51.980 --> 00:20:55.260
It's like just a
space time point.

00:20:55.260 --> 00:21:01.360
But how about this conform
in this Yang-Mills theory?

00:21:01.360 --> 00:21:06.430
What is the symmetry
of the object?

00:21:06.430 --> 00:21:08.660
What kind of object does
this symmetry correspond

00:21:08.660 --> 00:21:09.884
to because it seems--

00:21:09.884 --> 00:21:11.300
HONG LIU: It's
conformal symmetry.

00:21:16.010 --> 00:21:19.635
AUDIENCE: Conformal symmetry
of the component of the field?

00:21:19.635 --> 00:21:20.510
HONG LIU: No, no, no.

00:21:20.510 --> 00:21:23.745
It's the conformal symmetry
of the Minkowski space.

00:21:26.360 --> 00:21:29.277
So on this side, you
have isometry of AdS.

00:21:29.277 --> 00:21:31.193
On the other side, you
have conformal symmetry

00:21:31.193 --> 00:21:33.052
of the Minkowski space.

00:21:33.052 --> 00:21:35.510
So you're asking what are you
corresponding to on the field

00:21:35.510 --> 00:21:36.710
theory side, right?

00:21:36.710 --> 00:21:39.550
So that's mapped to
the conformal symmetry

00:21:39.550 --> 00:21:41.547
of the Minkowski space.

00:21:46.250 --> 00:21:50.500
AUDIENCE: So the
isometry is actually

00:21:50.500 --> 00:21:52.004
large gauge transformations.

00:21:52.004 --> 00:21:52.670
HONG LIU: Right.

00:21:57.007 --> 00:21:58.590
So the story actually
is more general.

00:22:03.367 --> 00:22:05.075
So the story actually
works more general.

00:22:05.075 --> 00:22:07.533
This is the statement for the
N equal to 4 super Yang-Mills

00:22:07.533 --> 00:22:09.170
theory.

00:22:09.170 --> 00:22:10.380
So the story is more general.

00:22:22.030 --> 00:22:27.730
So in the case which you
have, say, more general,

00:22:27.730 --> 00:22:32.640
say duality between
a CFT in d dimensions

00:22:32.640 --> 00:22:43.855
in Minkowski d with the AdS
d plus 1 dimensional gravity.

00:22:47.108 --> 00:22:52.270
In any such duality, then
you always have the conformal

00:22:52.270 --> 00:23:00.150
symmetry, which is SO(d, 2)
on this here mapped to AdS

00:23:00.150 --> 00:23:00.650
isometry.

00:23:09.030 --> 00:23:11.720
And any internal
gauge symmetry, say

00:23:11.720 --> 00:23:16.080
if you have some u(s)
global symmetry here,

00:23:16.080 --> 00:23:25.320
then this will be mapped
into a u(1) gauge symmetry.

00:23:32.880 --> 00:23:36.750
Again, in the sense that
this u(s) global symmetry can

00:23:36.750 --> 00:23:40.640
be considered as the global part
of this u(1) gauge symmetry,

00:23:40.640 --> 00:23:42.443
the part which does
not vanish at infinity.

00:23:45.500 --> 00:23:51.450
And it's always the case that
global supersymmetry here

00:23:51.450 --> 00:23:57.020
would be corresponding to
the local supersymmetry here.

00:23:57.020 --> 00:23:59.870
And also in exactly
the sense that

00:23:59.870 --> 00:24:03.500
even for the local
supersymmetric transformation

00:24:03.500 --> 00:24:05.370
in the gravity
side, there's also

00:24:05.370 --> 00:24:07.586
a part which does not
vanish at infinity.

00:24:07.586 --> 00:24:08.960
And that's the
part corresponding

00:24:08.960 --> 00:24:12.770
to the global supersymmetry
on the field theory side.

00:24:15.510 --> 00:24:16.350
Yes?

00:24:16.350 --> 00:24:21.924
AUDIENCE: What are the fermions
supersymmetry on the AdS side?

00:24:21.924 --> 00:24:22.590
HONG LIU: Sorry?

00:24:22.590 --> 00:24:25.310
AUDIENCE: In the low energy
limit on the AdS part,

00:24:25.310 --> 00:24:29.260
what are the fermion
supersymmetry?

00:24:29.260 --> 00:24:32.700
HONG LIU: It's the same thing.

00:24:32.700 --> 00:24:34.450
What do you mean,
what about fermions?

00:24:34.450 --> 00:24:37.042
So there will be some fermions.

00:24:37.042 --> 00:24:39.018
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE] fermions?

00:24:39.018 --> 00:24:42.480
So there is more than
gravitons on the AdS side

00:24:42.480 --> 00:24:43.820
involved in low energy limits?

00:24:43.820 --> 00:24:44.490
HONG LIU: Yeah.

00:24:44.490 --> 00:24:46.910
There are gravitons, and
there are also some fermions.

00:24:46.910 --> 00:24:48.535
There's something
called a [INAUDIBLE].

00:24:48.535 --> 00:24:51.420
There are some other
fermions, et cetera.

00:24:51.420 --> 00:24:54.569
AUDIENCE: Is it they who
carry the u(1) gauge charge?

00:24:54.569 --> 00:24:55.110
HONG LIU: No.

00:24:55.110 --> 00:24:56.090
Here is more general.

00:24:58.890 --> 00:25:06.430
In this case, indeed--
so this isometry of S5,

00:25:06.430 --> 00:25:11.740
once you deduce to AdS5, that
just again becomes a gauge

00:25:11.740 --> 00:25:13.860
symmetry, SO(6) gauge symmetry.

00:25:13.860 --> 00:25:19.170
And some fermions indeed are
charged on this SO(6) gauge

00:25:19.170 --> 00:25:21.440
symmetry.

00:25:21.440 --> 00:25:23.540
And here, it's
just more general.

00:25:23.540 --> 00:25:27.540
So whatever things, anytime if
you have some global symmetry

00:25:27.540 --> 00:25:32.900
here should be mapped to
some gauge symmetry here.

00:25:32.900 --> 00:25:37.742
And we will say this a little
bit more a little bit later.

00:25:37.742 --> 00:25:39.075
Do you have any other questions?

00:25:41.730 --> 00:25:45.720
So now let's move to the
matching of parameters.

00:25:45.720 --> 00:25:51.850
Again, this is
more like a review

00:25:51.850 --> 00:25:53.070
of what we discussed before.

00:25:56.120 --> 00:26:02.780
And again, first N equals to
4 super Yang-Mills theory.

00:26:02.780 --> 00:26:06.780
And then this is type
IIB on AdS5 times S5.

00:26:10.740 --> 00:26:14.870
So previously we said, from
the relation of the d-brane,

00:26:14.870 --> 00:26:19.530
so the G Yang-Mills square
here is related to the 4 pi GS

00:26:19.530 --> 00:26:22.070
here, string coupling.

00:26:22.070 --> 00:26:25.780
And also, from the
d3-brane solution,

00:26:25.780 --> 00:26:29.310
we find is that the
G Yang-Mills square--

00:26:29.310 --> 00:26:33.290
we find, for example,
here the curvature radius

00:26:33.290 --> 00:26:41.090
R has the following form, 4
pi GS and alpha prime squared.

00:26:41.090 --> 00:26:45.810
So the N is the
same N on this side.

00:26:45.810 --> 00:26:54.000
So the N is the gauge group N.
I should say the flux N. Anyway,

00:26:54.000 --> 00:26:57.140
let me add something.

00:26:57.140 --> 00:27:00.230
So the N is the number of
d-branes on this side which

00:27:00.230 --> 00:27:02.880
translate into the flux.

00:27:02.880 --> 00:27:06.050
So the flux N. And then
here is corresponding

00:27:06.050 --> 00:27:06.800
to you have SU(N).

00:27:12.040 --> 00:27:14.670
So this R, this
curvature radius is

00:27:14.670 --> 00:27:18.770
related to the alpha prime
squared and the gs in this way.

00:27:18.770 --> 00:27:25.760
And so on this side,
the dimension parameter

00:27:25.760 --> 00:27:28.680
is given by R squared
divided by alpha prime.

00:27:28.680 --> 00:27:32.800
So if you look at
this relation, if you

00:27:32.800 --> 00:27:35.960
look at alpha prime 4
to alpha prime squared,

00:27:35.960 --> 00:27:39.890
then you find this is
just relating the alpha.

00:27:39.890 --> 00:27:42.440
From this relation,
4 pi GS is equal just

00:27:42.440 --> 00:27:44.260
to G Yang-Mills square.

00:27:44.260 --> 00:27:47.622
And the N is N.
This is the relation

00:27:47.622 --> 00:27:48.580
between the parameters.

00:27:58.512 --> 00:27:59.720
Any questions regarding this?

00:28:06.200 --> 00:28:11.950
So on the gravity side, we said
these are the two parameters.

00:28:11.950 --> 00:28:14.410
And of course, you
also have this N.

00:28:14.410 --> 00:28:17.940
But these are the
two basic parameters.

00:28:17.940 --> 00:28:22.610
And we can also,
instead of using GS,

00:28:22.610 --> 00:28:26.190
as we said before, you can
also use the Newton constant.

00:28:26.190 --> 00:28:28.860
So the 10 dimensional
Newton constant

00:28:28.860 --> 00:28:31.510
is length dimension eight.

00:28:31.510 --> 00:28:35.950
Then the dimensionless parameter
would be GN divided by R

00:28:35.950 --> 00:28:36.875
to the power 8.

00:28:39.990 --> 00:28:44.529
And the GN is related to
the GS and alpha prime

00:28:44.529 --> 00:28:45.195
by this formula.

00:28:49.820 --> 00:28:53.105
So now you can just use
the relation between the GS

00:28:53.105 --> 00:28:57.550
to exactly translate this
into Yang-Mills coupling.

00:28:57.550 --> 00:29:00.140
You just can use this
relation and then use

00:29:00.140 --> 00:29:03.000
that to translate this into
the parameter in the Yang-Mills

00:29:03.000 --> 00:29:04.620
theory side.

00:29:04.620 --> 00:29:08.340
Then you find, once you
plug all those relations in,

00:29:08.340 --> 00:29:11.890
how the GS and alpha prime,
et cetera related to N,

00:29:11.890 --> 00:29:15.360
then you find here
actually, G Yang-Mills

00:29:15.360 --> 00:29:17.750
have disappeared
in this relation.

00:29:17.750 --> 00:29:21.900
What you find is that the
Newton constant essentially just

00:29:21.900 --> 00:29:24.730
related to 1 over N squared.

00:29:24.730 --> 00:29:29.710
Up to some parameter, just
related to 1 over N squared.

00:29:29.710 --> 00:29:33.121
So if you're expanding G Newton,
just like expanding 1 over N

00:29:33.121 --> 00:29:33.621
squared.

00:29:39.540 --> 00:29:49.880
So as we said before, we often
do dimensional reduction on S5.

00:29:58.160 --> 00:30:01.720
Let me get a five
dimensional Newton constant.

00:30:01.720 --> 00:30:03.220
So five dimensional
Newton constant

00:30:03.220 --> 00:30:06.770
is equal to the 10
dimensional Newton constant.

00:30:06.770 --> 00:30:09.370
And the difference
is the volume of S5.

00:30:18.340 --> 00:30:20.440
We wrote this down before.

00:30:20.440 --> 00:30:29.350
And the S5 is equal to pi
cubed R to the power fifth.

00:30:29.350 --> 00:30:32.940
And then from here,
you can just work out.

00:30:32.940 --> 00:30:36.578
So G5 has dimension 3.

00:30:36.578 --> 00:30:41.930
Then G5 divided by R cubed,
again only related to N given

00:30:41.930 --> 00:30:43.540
by pi divided by 2N squared.

00:30:53.450 --> 00:30:55.730
So these relations are
often useful in the future.

00:31:12.060 --> 00:31:17.275
So now let's look at [INAUDIBLE]
limits of this relation.

00:31:21.660 --> 00:31:23.680
So let's first look at
the classical gravity

00:31:23.680 --> 00:31:24.950
limit on the gravity side.

00:31:37.601 --> 00:31:42.860
As we discussed at the beginning
of this class, by classic,

00:31:42.860 --> 00:31:47.870
we always use h bar equal to 1.

00:31:47.870 --> 00:31:49.913
So our h bar is
always equal to 1.

00:31:54.020 --> 00:31:57.850
But quantum gravity is
captured by this parameter,

00:31:57.850 --> 00:32:00.590
h bar times GN.

00:32:00.590 --> 00:32:04.250
So even though h bar equal
to 1, in the limit when

00:32:04.250 --> 00:32:07.240
GN goes to zero, then
you are in the regime

00:32:07.240 --> 00:32:10.330
in which you can ignore
the quantum gravity effect.

00:32:10.330 --> 00:32:13.950
So that's what we mean by
the classical gravity limit

00:32:13.950 --> 00:32:16.890
is that this should go to
zero, and then alpha prime

00:32:16.890 --> 00:32:19.410
should go to zero.

00:32:19.410 --> 00:32:22.450
So this means the string
effect is not important.

00:32:22.450 --> 00:32:28.120
And this is all
in the unit of R.

00:32:28.120 --> 00:32:30.630
And here, when I
write these relations,

00:32:30.630 --> 00:32:35.030
I have all set h bar equal to 1.

00:32:35.030 --> 00:32:37.130
So when I say the
classical gravity limit,

00:32:37.130 --> 00:32:40.590
which is this limit in
which h bar equal to 1,

00:32:40.590 --> 00:32:44.940
but the effect of the Newton
constant goes to zero.

00:32:44.940 --> 00:32:49.160
And the reason I emphasize it
is that if you have some matter

00:32:49.160 --> 00:32:55.330
field in this geometry, then
those matter fields should

00:32:55.330 --> 00:32:58.230
be treated as full quantum.

00:32:58.230 --> 00:33:01.712
Just don't treat the
gravity as quantum,

00:33:01.712 --> 00:33:04.420
but those matter fields
should be treated as quantum.

00:33:04.420 --> 00:33:05.830
So the classical
gravity limit is

00:33:05.830 --> 00:33:11.495
the same as QFT, Quantum Field
Theory in curved space time.

00:33:17.410 --> 00:33:19.250
So gravity does not fluctuate.

00:33:19.250 --> 00:33:22.180
So you have rigid
curved space time.

00:33:22.180 --> 00:33:26.840
But your matter field can
fluctuate, h bar equal to 1.

00:33:26.840 --> 00:33:30.110
So essentially, we are
dealing with quantum field

00:33:30.110 --> 00:33:32.410
theory in curved space time.

00:33:32.410 --> 00:33:38.430
So in the type
IIB super gravity,

00:33:38.430 --> 00:33:40.920
there are many, many such
kind of matter fields,

00:33:40.920 --> 00:33:44.560
and they all should be
treated quantum mechanically.

00:33:48.800 --> 00:33:51.940
It's just that you should
consider this small.

00:33:51.940 --> 00:33:55.300
So let's consider
what this means.

00:33:55.300 --> 00:34:01.140
So GN small as a
dimensionless parameter,

00:34:01.140 --> 00:34:06.540
this translates into
field theory side

00:34:06.540 --> 00:34:08.409
if we use this relation.

00:34:08.409 --> 00:34:11.130
So that means N
goes to infinity.

00:34:11.130 --> 00:34:14.475
So this is the large N limit
of the Yang-Mills theory.

00:34:14.475 --> 00:34:16.600
This is the large N limit
of the Yang-Mills theory.

00:34:19.179 --> 00:34:20.783
And then alpha
prime goes to zero.

00:34:25.170 --> 00:34:29.620
From the relation between
the alpha prime and here,

00:34:29.620 --> 00:34:33.819
when alpha prime goes to zero,
so this is in the downstairs.

00:34:33.819 --> 00:34:35.610
Then that means this
should go to infinity.

00:34:38.190 --> 00:34:43.020
So this is the t Hooft
coupling we defined before.

00:34:43.020 --> 00:34:45.390
So this means the t Hooft
coupling goes to infinity.

00:34:52.909 --> 00:34:54.677
So now we see a
remarkable relation.

00:35:04.690 --> 00:35:08.490
So this is what we expect.

00:35:08.490 --> 00:35:12.080
If you still remember what we
did before in the large N gauge

00:35:12.080 --> 00:35:15.600
theory, in the large N gauge
theory in the large N limit,

00:35:15.600 --> 00:35:18.100
the fluctuations become
very small, et cetera.

00:35:18.100 --> 00:35:21.160
So this is consistent
that on the gravity side,

00:35:21.160 --> 00:35:25.990
the fluctuation in the
geometry is very small.

00:35:25.990 --> 00:35:33.890
And now, we see that the
decoupling of the string effect

00:35:33.890 --> 00:35:38.530
requires on the field theory
side the strong coupling.

00:35:38.530 --> 00:35:42.410
This is also something
roughly we said before.

00:35:42.410 --> 00:35:49.710
Remember, when we talked
about large N gauge theory,

00:35:49.710 --> 00:35:51.640
large N gauge theory,
you have planar diagram,

00:35:51.640 --> 00:35:55.040
non-planar diagram, et cetera.

00:35:55.040 --> 00:35:57.930
And at each level, say
at the planar diagram,

00:35:57.930 --> 00:36:01.380
you need to sum over infinite
number of [INAUDIBLE] diagrams

00:36:01.380 --> 00:36:04.499
which are all planar topology.

00:36:04.499 --> 00:36:07.040
And if you look at just those
[INAUDIBLE] diagrams, of course

00:36:07.040 --> 00:36:11.009
you don't see a space
time interpretation

00:36:11.009 --> 00:36:12.800
because they are just
[INAUDIBLE] diagrams.

00:36:12.800 --> 00:36:16.080
You don't see a
continuous surface.

00:36:16.080 --> 00:36:20.080
And I already alluded before
that the continuous surface

00:36:20.080 --> 00:36:23.089
can emerge if that
diagram becomes

00:36:23.089 --> 00:36:24.130
sufficiently complicated.

00:36:26.936 --> 00:36:29.310
And the way to make that
diagram sufficiently complicated

00:36:29.310 --> 00:36:32.330
is to make it to be
a strong coupling.

00:36:32.330 --> 00:36:34.910
The strong coupling,
then the diagram

00:36:34.910 --> 00:36:37.670
with many, many
vertices will dominate.

00:36:37.670 --> 00:36:40.470
And then the most dominated
diagrams are those diagrams

00:36:40.470 --> 00:36:42.000
with not a lot of vertices.

00:36:42.000 --> 00:36:45.600
And they essentially are
going to continue to limits.

00:36:45.600 --> 00:36:50.070
And so this relation
[INAUDIBLE] realizes

00:36:50.070 --> 00:36:52.380
that kind of intuition.

00:36:52.380 --> 00:36:56.230
If you don't remember, go
back to your loads regarding

00:36:56.230 --> 00:36:57.280
the large N gauge theory.

00:37:01.680 --> 00:37:04.140
So this relation
is also remarkable

00:37:04.140 --> 00:37:07.350
for the following reason.

00:37:07.350 --> 00:37:09.620
Because this limit on the
gravity side is simple,

00:37:09.620 --> 00:37:12.540
we can just deal
with quantum field

00:37:12.540 --> 00:37:16.610
theory in the curved space
time, which we know how to do.

00:37:16.610 --> 00:37:18.640
But on this side, it's
highly non-trivial

00:37:18.640 --> 00:37:21.030
because this is an
infinite coupling limit.

00:37:21.030 --> 00:37:31.860
So this will tell you that
the strong coupling limit is

00:37:31.860 --> 00:37:40.354
described by classical gravity.

00:37:52.480 --> 00:37:56.340
So that means that we can
actually use classical gravity

00:37:56.340 --> 00:37:59.404
to, in principle, solve problems
which are strongly coupled.

00:38:07.840 --> 00:38:10.470
So also, of course, there
are corrections beyond this.

00:38:13.710 --> 00:38:24.610
So quantum gravity
corrections on this side,

00:38:24.610 --> 00:38:26.760
so this is a classical
gravity limit

00:38:26.760 --> 00:38:29.400
if you take those
parameters to go to zero.

00:38:29.400 --> 00:38:32.620
But suppose those parameters
are not zero, just small.

00:38:32.620 --> 00:38:35.110
Then you can just expand
in those parameters.

00:38:35.110 --> 00:38:39.540
For example, can you
expand in GN divided by 8.

00:38:39.540 --> 00:38:42.760
And that expansion essentially
gives you quantum gravity

00:38:42.760 --> 00:38:45.600
corrections [INAUDIBLE].

00:38:45.600 --> 00:38:51.055
And now, from this relation,
the expansion of GN

00:38:51.055 --> 00:38:53.290
then is translated.

00:38:53.290 --> 00:39:00.470
So this is expansion
in G Newton.

00:39:00.470 --> 00:39:02.390
So from that
relation, we see this

00:39:02.390 --> 00:39:07.170
has become the expansion 1 over
N squared in the field theory

00:39:07.170 --> 00:39:07.670
side.

00:39:14.830 --> 00:39:24.096
Just expansion 1 over N squared.

00:39:29.850 --> 00:39:33.500
So on this side, you can
also take into account

